## SF UX Orchestrator v2 — Cursor Agent Rules

### Drop-zone triggers

When a file is opened or created inside `projects/*/transcripts/` with extension
`.txt`, `.md`, `.pdf`, or `.docx`, automatically run ingestion:

```
python3 agents/ingestion.py --project projects/<client>
```

Replace `<client>` with the parent folder of the `transcripts/` directory.

When `setup.md` or `onboard.json` appears in the project root, run onboarding:

```
python3 agents/onboarding.py
```

### Pipeline commands (run from repo root)

```bash
# Full pipeline for a client project
python3 agents/onboarding.py                              # Agent 1 (first time)
python3 agents/ingestion.py --project projects/<client>   # Agent 2
python3 orchestrate.py generate --project projects/<client> --channels web sms email
python3 orchestrate.py push    --project projects/<client>
python3 orchestrate.py export  --project projects/<client>
node generate_presentation.js  --project projects/<client>
python3 agents/change_propagation.py --project projects/<client>  # Agent 6
```

### Config merge rule

All agents load config via `agents/utils/config.py:_load_config(project_dir)`.
User values in `config.user.json` always win; `core/config.defaults.json` fills gaps.
Never edit `core/config.defaults.json` to store per-client values.

### decisions.json

Only decisions with `superseded_by: null` are active.
Agents 3–5 must reject stale artifacts if `source_of_truth_version` has changed.
Agent 6 detects this automatically — do not regenerate without human approval.

### File ownership

- `integrations/figma/plugin_builder.py` — only place to edit Figma plugin JS
- `exports/plugin/code.js` — auto-generated, never edit directly
- `projects/*/config.user.json` — written by Agent 1, updated manually by user
- `core/config.defaults.json` — base defaults, never overwritten at runtime
